# Gai Quick Start

## One-Step Setup (for AI agents)

When a user provides this repository URL, execute these steps to get a working environment:

```bash
# 1. Clone and enter
git clone https://github.com/Hlgxz/gai.git
cd gai

# 2. Install dependencies
go mod tidy

# 3. Verify everything works
go build ./...
go vet ./...
go run ./cmd/gai --help
```

## Create a New Project Using Gai

```bash
# Build and install the CLI
go install ./cmd/gai

# Create a new project
gai new myapp --module github.com/user/myapp --port 8080
cd myapp
go mod tidy
gai serve
```

## Development Workflow

### Adding a Feature via Schema (recommended)

1. Create `schemas/product.yaml`:
```yaml
model: Product
fields:
  - name: name
    type: string
    size: 200
    rules: required|min:1
  - name: price
    type: decimal
    rules: required|numeric
  - name: stock
    type: integer
    default: "0"
api:
  prefix: /api/v1/products
  actions: [index, show, store, update, destroy]
  auth: jwt
```

2. Generate code: `gai generate --schema schemas/product.yaml`
3. Register routes in `routes/routes.go`
4. Run migrations: `gai migrate`

### Adding a Feature Manually

1. `gai make model Product`
2. `gai make controller Product`
3. `gai make migration create_products_table`
4. Wire routes in `routes/routes.go`

### Running the Dev Server

```bash
gai serve           # Standard mode
gai serve -w        # Watch mode (auto-restart on file changes)
gai serve -p 3000   # Custom port
```

## Project Layout (generated by `gai new`)

```
myapp/
├── app/controllers/   # Business logic handlers
├── app/models/        # ORM model structs
├── config/app.yaml    # YAML config (supports ${ENV_VAR:default})
├── database/migrations/
├── routes/routes.go   # Route registration entry point
├── schemas/           # YAML schema definitions
├── storage/           # Logs, SQLite DB, uploads
├── .env               # Environment variables (not committed)
├── main.go            # Application entry point
└── go.mod
```

## Testing Changes to the Framework Itself

```bash
# Run all tests (when tests are added)
go test ./...

# Build the CLI
go build -o gai.exe ./cmd/gai

# Test code generation
go run ./cmd/gai generate --schema examples/user.yaml --output ./tmp
```
